          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Federal Employee Accountability Act of 2019 or FEAA</b></p> <p> <p>This bill provides additional statutory authority for federal agencies to discipline employees.<p>Specifically, agencies may remove or demote (i.e., reduce the grade or pay of) employees for performance or misconduct without proving that the adverse action promotes the efficiency of the service. <p>The bill provides a statutory definition of the term &quot;misconduct.&quot; <p>An adverse action may be appealed to the Merit Systems Protection Board. The bill sets forth requirements and procedures for such appeals.]]></text>
        </item>
